data.title: Western Harbour Tunnel and Sydney Harbour Tunnel Asset Management Services
data.meta_description: This contract covers Asset Management Services for the Sydney Harbour Tunnel and future Western Harbour Tunnel.
data.text:
This contract covers Asset Management Services for the Sydney Harbour Tunnel and future Western Harbour Tunnel. The scope of the contract includes:

asset management

operations

maintenance, and

lifecycle services for the two assets.

This contract is also expected to form a key part in supporting the delivery of the Western Harbour Tunnel and Beaches Link program.

The Sydney Harbour Tunnel is maintained and operated under a 30-year concession, which was awarded in 1987, commenced in 1992, and is set to expire in 2022. The Western Harbour Tunnel will link the WestConnex Rozelle Interchange with North Sydney and the future Beaches Link through the Warringah Freeway Upgrade.
